    "However, the BG, N, P, S combination indicated a decrease in accuracy at 87.01% and 85.71%, along with precision, recall, and F1-score values of 89.16%, 87.01%, 87.30% and 85.88%, 85.71%, 85.78% for each data split respectively.",
    "The performance for 3-class and 2-class classification showed a range of accuracy scores, with the 2-class case achieving 100% accuracy for the N, D combination in both data splits, with corresponding precision, recall, and F1-score values also being 100%.",
    "Data augmentation is applied exclusively to the training set to enhance the model's generalization by introducing a broader range of variations, thereby preventing overfitting.",
    "This approach ensures the model learns from a diverse dataset, improving its predictive performance on unseen data.",
